 spaces, as well as geographical areas. Tracing these concepts of historical space, this volume demonstrates that the image works as a powerful tool to propagate the ideology of German imperialism in the nineteenth-century, but also can critically reflect the political agendas of national historicism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aArt and history -- Germany -- History -- 19th century. 0aArt and historyzGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 0aArt and society -- Germany -- History -- 19th century. 0aArt and societyzGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 0aHistoricism in art. 0aHistoriography -- Germany -- History -- 19th century. 0aHistoriographyzGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 4aBurckhardt, Jacob. 4aHistorismus. 4aRanke, Leopold von. 4aRaum. 4aVisualität. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aBurckhardt, Jacob.  aHistoricism.  aRanke, Leopold von.  aSpace.  aVisuality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE LITERATURE 2013z978311031726808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2013z9783110317251oZDB-23-DLW0 cprintz978311028282540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028293140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110282931423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110282931/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-031726-8  E-BOOK PACKAGE LITERATURE 2013b2013  aEBA_BACKALL